{"title":"Swing Left or Right with the Same Rig’d RambleSwing Swingout Hitch Rack Adapter","link":"https://bikerumor.com/rigd-rambleswing-swingout-hitch-rack-adapter-left-right-swing/","date":1706549541000,"content":"<p><img width=\"1280\" height=\"720\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Rigd-RambleSwing-hitchrack-logo-in-the-wild.jpeg\" alt=\"Rig'd RambleSwing hitchrack logo in the wild\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Rigd-RambleSwing-hitchrack-logo-in-the-wild.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Rigd-RambleSwing-hitchrack-logo-in-the-wild-297x167.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Rigd-RambleSwing-hitchrack-logo-in-the-wild-800x450.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Rigd-RambleSwing-hitchrack-logo-in-the-wild-120x68.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Rigd-RambleSwing-hitchrack-logo-in-the-wild-768x432.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Rigd-RambleSwing-hitchrack-logo-in-the-wild-1200x675.jpeg 1200w\" /></p>\n<p>Founded by people with a passion for off-roading and riding bikes, Rig’d Supply is a company that offers both of those worlds some quality gear. Headquartered in Orange, California, their <a href=\"https://www.rigdsupply.com/products/rambleswing-bike-rack-swing-out\" target=\"_blank\">latest </a>offering is the RambleSwing, a heavy-duty swing-out hitch adapter that reflects the company’s two passions in a nice, neat package. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><img width=\"800\" height=\"800\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Rigd-RambleSwing-hitchrack-on-Jeep-JL-800x800.jpeg\" alt=\"Rig'd RambleSwing hitchrack on Jeep JL\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Rigd-RambleSwing-hitchrack-on-Jeep-JL-800x800.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Rigd-RambleSwing-hitchrack-on-Jeep-JL-297x297.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Rigd-RambleSwing-hitchrack-on-Jeep-JL-120x120.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Rigd-RambleSwing-hitchrack-on-Jeep-JL-768x768.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Rigd-RambleSwing-hitchrack-on-Jeep-JL.jpeg 1280w\" /><figcaption>(Photo/Rig’d Supply) Jeep JL</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Rigd-RambleSwing-hitchrack-on-bronco-800x533.jpeg\" alt=\"Rig'd RambleSwing hitchrack on bronco\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Rigd-RambleSwing-hitchrack-on-bronco-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Rigd-RambleSwing-hitchrack-on-bronco-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Rigd-RambleSwing-hitchrack-on-bronco-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Rigd-RambleSwing-hitchrack-on-bronco-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Rigd-RambleSwing-hitchrack-on-bronco-720x480.jpeg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Rigd-RambleSwing-hitchrack-on-bronco.jpeg 1280w\" /><figcaption>Ford Bronco</figcaption></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Rig’d RambleSwing is a swing-out hitch rack accessory that was tailor-made for vehicles with a rear-mounted, full-size spare tire like the <a href=\"https://www.rigdsupply.com/blogs/news/best-bike-rack-swing-out-for-jeep-wrangler\" target=\"_blank\">Jeep Wrangler</a> and Ford Bronco. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"800\" height=\"332\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Rigd-RambleSwing-hitchrack-studio-closed-e1706292592392-800x332.jpeg\" alt=\"Rig'd RambleSwing hitchrack studio closed\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Rigd-RambleSwing-hitchrack-studio-closed-e1706292592392-800x332.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Rigd-RambleSwing-hitchrack-studio-closed-e1706292592392-297x123.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Rigd-RambleSwing-hitchrack-studio-closed-e1706292592392-120x50.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Rigd-RambleSwing-hitchrack-studio-closed-e1706292592392-768x319.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Rigd-RambleSwing-hitchrack-studio-closed-e1706292592392.jpeg 1280w\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>It will work with any <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/best-hitch-bike-racks/\">hitch-stye bike rack</a> you may have and will add the utility of being able to swing it away from the vehicle to access the vehicle’s rear cargo area. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><img width=\"800\" height=\"600\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Rigd-RambleSwing-hitchrack-studio-open-800x600.jpeg\" alt=\"Rig'd RambleSwing hitchrack studio open\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Rigd-RambleSwing-hitchrack-studio-open-800x600.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Rigd-RambleSwing-hitchrack-studio-open-297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Rigd-RambleSwing-hitchrack-studio-open-120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Rigd-RambleSwing-hitchrack-studio-open-768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Rigd-RambleSwing-hitchrack-studio-open.jpeg 1280w\" /><figcaption>RambleSwing open…</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"800\" height=\"638\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Rigd-RambleSwing-hitchrack-studio-closed-from-the-back-800x638.jpeg\" alt=\"Rig'd RambleSwing hitchrack studio closed from the back\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Rigd-RambleSwing-hitchrack-studio-closed-from-the-back-800x638.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Rigd-RambleSwing-hitchrack-studio-closed-from-the-back-297x237.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Rigd-RambleSwing-hitchrack-studio-closed-from-the-back-120x96.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Rigd-RambleSwing-hitchrack-studio-closed-from-the-back-768x612.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Rigd-RambleSwing-hitchrack-studio-closed-from-the-back.jpeg 1280w\" /><figcaption>and closed</figcaption></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The RambleSwing became available back in the Fall of 2023. It’s burly, with a purposely over-engineered design made to withstand the heaviest bikes on the harshest trails. Boasting a 300lb weight limit, this means the heaviest eBike will be supported.  </p>\n\n\n\n<p>It’s compatible with all 2″ hitch-mounted bike racks, but Rig’d prefers that you pair it with their bike rack, the <a href=\"https://www.rigdsupply.com/collections/ramblerack-heavy-duty-hitch-bike-rack\" target=\"_blank\">RambleRack</a>. The Rig’d RambleSwing has some handy and unique features. </p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Rig’d RambleSwing Features</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"800\" height=\"414\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Rigd-RambleSwing-hitchrack-glide-closeup-e1706292884775-800x414.jpeg\" alt=\"Rig'd RambleSwing hitchrack glide closeup\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Rigd-RambleSwing-hitchrack-glide-closeup-e1706292884775-800x414.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Rigd-RambleSwing-hitchrack-glide-closeup-e1706292884775-297x154.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Rigd-RambleSwing-hitchrack-glide-closeup-e1706292884775-120x62.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Rigd-RambleSwing-hitchrack-glide-closeup-e1706292884775-768x398.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Rigd-RambleSwing-hitchrack-glide-closeup-e1706292884775.jpeg 1280w\" /><figcaption>Close-up of the Delrin Glide Plates</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>In-Line-Design:</strong> The RambleSwing’s in-line design creates a stiff connection between the two arms, sandwiched by a set of Delrin glide plates to help with easy closure.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"800\" height=\"534\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Rigd-RambleSwing-hitchrack-hitch-coseup-800x534.jpeg\" alt=\"Rig'd RambleSwing hitchrack hitch coseup\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Rigd-RambleSwing-hitchrack-hitch-coseup-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Rigd-RambleSwing-hitchrack-hitch-coseup-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Rigd-RambleSwing-hitchrack-hitch-coseup-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Rigd-RambleSwing-hitchrack-hitch-coseup-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Rigd-RambleSwing-hitchrack-hitch-coseup-720x480.jpeg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Rigd-RambleSwing-hitchrack-hitch-coseup.jpeg 1280w\" /><figcaption>Close-up of the hitch and the reversible step located on both sides. </figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>FlipFlop™ Technology:</strong> “FlipFlop” technology allows the user to swing it open to the left (driver side) or right (passenger side) by simply flipping the swing over. This could come in handy if the rack blocks your exhaust pipe on one side but not the other. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"800\" height=\"349\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Rigd-RambleSwing-hitchrack-step-and-wedge-e1706293050492-800x349.jpeg\" alt=\"Rig'd RambleSwing hitchrack step and wedge\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Rigd-RambleSwing-hitchrack-step-and-wedge-e1706293050492-800x349.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Rigd-RambleSwing-hitchrack-step-and-wedge-e1706293050492-297x129.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Rigd-RambleSwing-hitchrack-step-and-wedge-e1706293050492-120x52.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Rigd-RambleSwing-hitchrack-step-and-wedge-e1706293050492-768x335.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Rigd-RambleSwing-hitchrack-step-and-wedge-e1706293050492.jpeg 1280w\" /><figcaption>Close-up of the anti-wobble wedge</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Wobble-Free™:</strong> The adapter features the same wobble-free wedge system as their <a href=\"https://www.rigdsupply.com/collections/ultraswing\" target=\"_blank\">UltraSwing</a> to eliminate movement in the vehicle’s hitch.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"800\" height=\"380\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Rigd-RambleSwing-hitchrack-compression-latch-closeup-e1706293143872-800x380.jpeg\" alt=\"Rig'd RambleSwing hitchrack compression latch closeup\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Rigd-RambleSwing-hitchrack-compression-latch-closeup-e1706293143872-800x380.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Rigd-RambleSwing-hitchrack-compression-latch-closeup-e1706293143872-297x141.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Rigd-RambleSwing-hitchrack-compression-latch-closeup-e1706293143872-120x57.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Rigd-RambleSwing-hitchrack-compression-latch-closeup-e1706293143872-768x365.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Rigd-RambleSwing-hitchrack-compression-latch-closeup-e1706293143872.jpeg 1280w\" /><figcaption>Close-up of the compression latch</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>The Ultimate Latch:</strong> They use a patented bike-grip handled 500 lb <a href=\"https://www.rigdsupply.com/products/ultraswing-latch\" target=\"_blank\">compression latch</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Rigd-RambleSwing-hitchrack-step-in-use-800x533.jpeg\" alt=\"Rig'd RambleSwing hitchrack step in use\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Rigd-RambleSwing-hitchrack-step-in-use-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Rigd-RambleSwing-hitchrack-step-in-use-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Rigd-RambleSwing-hitchrack-step-in-use-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Rigd-RambleSwing-hitchrack-step-in-use-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Rigd-RambleSwing-hitchrack-step-in-use-720x480.jpeg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Rigd-RambleSwing-hitchrack-step-in-use.jpeg 1280w\" /><figcaption>Step in use</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Integrated Step:</strong> RambleSwing also features an integrated step on both sides, adding convenience when you need easy access to your truck, van, or SUV.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"800\" height=\"280\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Rigd-RambleSwing-hitchrack-special-batteship-grip-tape-e1706293236512-800x280.jpeg\" alt=\"Rig'd RambleSwing hitchrack special batteship grip tape\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Rigd-RambleSwing-hitchrack-special-batteship-grip-tape-e1706293236512-800x280.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Rigd-RambleSwing-hitchrack-special-batteship-grip-tape-e1706293236512-297x104.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Rigd-RambleSwing-hitchrack-special-batteship-grip-tape-e1706293236512-120x42.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Rigd-RambleSwing-hitchrack-special-batteship-grip-tape-e1706293236512-768x269.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Rigd-RambleSwing-hitchrack-special-batteship-grip-tape-e1706293236512.jpeg 1280w\" /><figcaption>Close-up, Battleship Griptape</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Battleship Grip:</strong> On the integrated step Rig’d utilizes a super-durable Jessup grip tape. This type of tape was originally developed for use on the decks of battleships.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"800\" height=\"329\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Rigd-RambleSwing-hitchrack-pivot-e1706293318476-800x329.jpeg\" alt=\"Rig'd RambleSwing hitchrack pivot\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Rigd-RambleSwing-hitchrack-pivot-e1706293318476-800x329.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Rigd-RambleSwing-hitchrack-pivot-e1706293318476-297x122.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Rigd-RambleSwing-hitchrack-pivot-e1706293318476-120x49.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Rigd-RambleSwing-hitchrack-pivot-e1706293318476-768x316.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Rigd-RambleSwing-hitchrack-pivot-e1706293318476.jpeg 1280w\" /><figcaption>All parts are replaceable</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Made in the USA: </strong>The Ramble Swing is completely rebuildable with all pieces available to repair and is backed by their <a href=\"https://www.rigdsupply.com/pages/rigd-ramble-for-life-warranty\">Ramble for Life Warranty</a> </p>\n\n\n\n<p>I recently spoke with Luke over at Rig’d, and since they are local to me, I will be picking up a RambleSwing to review on my Jeep Wrangler JL. I’ll be reviewing it while using my <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/rocky-mounts-guide-rail-tray-style-bike-rack-review-like-1up/\" target=\"_blank\">Rocky Mounts Guide Rail</a>. After that, I will follow it up with a review of their <a href=\"https://www.rigdsupply.com/products/rigd-ramblerack-1-heavy-duty-hitch-bike-rack?variant=43890156765404\" target=\"_blank\">RambleRack</a> with the 2-Bike Pivot system. Stay tuned here for my first impressions of the RambleSwing in the next week or so. </p>\n\n\n\n<h2>RambleSwing Tech Specs and Retail</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Rigd-RambleSwing-hitchrack-open-in-use-800x533.jpeg\" alt=\"Rig'd RambleSwing hitchrack open in use\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Rigd-RambleSwing-hitchrack-open-in-use-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Rigd-RambleSwing-hitchrack-open-in-use-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Rigd-RambleSwing-hitchrack-open-in-use-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Rigd-RambleSwing-hitchrack-open-in-use-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Rigd-RambleSwing-hitchrack-open-in-use-720x480.jpeg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Rigd-RambleSwing-hitchrack-open-in-use.jpeg 1280w\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Retail: $799</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>300 lb max load rating</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Compatible with all 2″ hitch-mounted bike racks</li>\n\n\n\n<li>90° and 120° locking open positions</li>\n\n\n\n<li>RambleSwing weight: 60 lbs</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Total width closed: 27″</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Zinc-rich primed and black semi-gloss powder-coated</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.rigdsupply.com/\" target=\"_blank\"><em>RigdSupply.com</em></a></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/rigd-rambleswing-swingout-hitch-rack-adapter-left-right-swing/\">Swing Left or Right with the Same Rig’d RambleSwing Swingout Hitch Rack Adapter</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Ron Frazelle","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"b375dac838ae66f8ec72d3d9090094645cb13e3a3e33df648ce8e823c2533e7b","category":"Cycling"}